# Atlas scheduler — cron entry
#
# Laravel's scheduler (routes/console.php) defines six recurring jobs, but
# nothing invokes `php artisan schedule:run` in production on its own — this
# single crontab line is what makes that happen, checked every minute so
# each job fires at its own configured cadence.
#
# Install: copy this line into the crontab of the user that owns the
# deployment (matching infrastructure/supervisor/atlas-worker.conf's
# `user=www-data`), e.g. via `crontab -e` as that user, or drop this file
# into /etc/cron.d/ (as root-owned, 644, with the user column below
# uncommented) — pick whichever your provisioning tooling already manages.
#
# /etc/cron.d/ form (six columns, user-column included):
# * * * * * www-data cd /var/www/atlas/backend && php artisan schedule:run >> /dev/null 2>&1
#
# Per-user crontab form (five columns, no user column):
* * * * * cd /var/www/atlas/backend && php artisan schedule:run >> /dev/null 2>&1
